Body:
Hast thou not seen how thy Lord hath spread the shade. And if He
			willed He could have made it still, then We have made the sun its
			pilot;

And He it is Who hath given independence to the two seas (though
			they meet); one palatable, sweet, and the other saltish, bitter;
			and hath set a bar and a forbidding ban between them.

The (faithful) slaves of the Beneficent are they who walk upon
			the earth modestly, and when the foolish ones address them
			answer: Peace;
